TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Description: Lets you select the basic lateral definition type.
TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Name: Lateral type

TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Description: Lets you specify whether to use the nearest available lane index if the defined lane index is not available in the current road lane section.
TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Name: Force to road

TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Description:
Specifies the value for the selected constant behavior type.
If you specify a lane index relative to the lane of the vehicle at segment start, positive lane indices indicate a lane change to the left of the vehicle and negative lane indices a lane change to the right of the vehicle. This behavior is independent from the lane index interpretation setting in the scenario properties.
TrafficEditorPropertyReference.Name: Constant
